<br>
From that room facing the room with the ramp that goes up to your right, go up the ramps, when you see the room on your LEFT with 5 dogs, the next room to your left with 3 dogs is the room where Jelek Icepaw spawns.  He spawns in the middle of the 3 dogs there, typically his placeholder is an icepaw cleric, but not always.  Jelek is a paladin so he will LOH.<br>
<br>
He's not too tough if you have a well balanced group, and slow him.  Usually you need to be level 55+ to get the sword on your own.  Sometimes people will ooc for someone to get it if it drops in their group and there are no paladins.  I know because ive done it with the sword of pain several times, sometimes i just let it rot.  I've seen a level 24 shadowknight walk down there and loot it.  I guess you could hang out and wait for someone to ooc it, but don't hold your breath.  Because honestly, when i see level 25 people looting that kind of equipment it sort of annoys me.<br>
<br>
But... there's always a chance if you wanna try that route.<br>
